                Elder abuse is described as "a single or repeated act, or a failure to act appropriately, that causes harm or distress to an older person in any relationship where there is an expectation of trust." Abuse of the elderly can take many forms, including financial, physical, psychological, and sexual. It may also be caused by deliberate or accidental negligence.
